HEADWORD: Zymome
<hw>Zy"mome</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>zy`mwma</grk> a fermented mixture.]</ety> <fld>(Old Chem.)</fld>
<def>A glutinous substance, insoluble in alcohol, resembling legumin; --
now called <altname>vegetable fibrin</altname>, <altname>vegetable
albumin</altname>, or <altname>gluten casein</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

